  "commentary": "With SPX at 7087.77 in PIN regime, dealers are positioned between the flip at 6996 and the massive +7089M gamma wall at 7200, creating strong stabilizing forces that should contain the current -9.6% 5-min selloff. The negative gamma pocket at 7115 means dealers will buy any dip toward that level, while the stacked positive gamma walls at 7100/7150/7200 create significant resistance above, especially as we approach the max gamma at 7200 where dealer selling pressure intensifies. Watch for mean reversion back toward 7100-7150 as the PIN regime and massive positive gamma exposure should dampen volatility and attract buying on this dip.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to stabilize and grind back up toward 7150 as dealers defend the downside.",
